			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good link for the N50.  But it left out 2 key things:
<br />

<br />
1.  After you define the macro, adjust the bands up so that the Archery one is as small as possible.  This prevents you from accidently shooting a merchant with an arrow.
<br />

<br />
2.  Define the lower band as Kick.  Nothing like Auto-Archery one way, Auto-Kick the other.
<br />

<br />
So, using my key board to draw(please bear with me), your finished macro should look like this:
<br />

<br />
        
<br />
        ______________
<br />
        |       Archery   
<br />
        |_____________
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |         OFF         
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |                       
<br />
        |_____________
<br />
        |        Kick         
<br />
        |_____________
<br />

<br />
You'll understand once you start to do it, it's not hard.  
<br />

<br />
PS.  You can adjust the bands by hovering your cursor over the line and draging it.  Just like resizing a window.<br />_________________<br />Hunter Rathmorg Vilesilencer
<br />
62nd Hunter for the
<br />
Court of the Crosswinds, FV
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=652272" target="_blank" class="postlink">My Gear</a></span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
